posts.name: Jim Sokoloff
posts.cooked:
I’ve got some WAgo 221s around and, if you absolutely don’t want to try CADing it yourself, I can either help you do it or CAD it up for you. (I’ll need a few more pics than that.)

Honestly, this is about as low complexity as a CAD design for FRC comes. I really would encourage you to tackle this within your team as a learning exercise, but I also don’t want to let you starve if you just need a darn fish and don’t want to learn how to fish.

Edit to add: This one actually seems more useful to me for a lot of use cases, using the inline 221s.

And piles of them on printables , including some with integrated zip tie holes .
